Python elementary is a new widget gui library introduced into Enlightenment libraries.

It was specifically built for small physical screens, where you dont need really 
care about the resolution or the high dpi.

Here are the official wiki (currently images are missing):
http://trac.enlightenment.org/e/wiki/Elementary

Dos1 compiled the html pages from docstrings:
http://openmoko.opendevice.org/~dos/elementary/

The source in enlightenment svn:
http://trac.enlightenment.org/e/browser/trunk/BINDINGS/python/python-elementary

There is an elementary demo app, where nearly every widget are presented:
(the test dir in python-elementary source)
http://trac.enlightenment.org/e/browser/trunk/BINDINGS/python/python-elementary/tests

